## Key Findings Summary

| Question | Finding |
|----------|---------|
| Win32 in GameEngine? | Yes — PreRTS.h includes windows.h + dinput.h for all TUs; GameEngine.cpp uses `timeGetTime`, ATL `_Module`, `HINSTANCE`, `HWND` |
| Win32 isolated to GameEngineDevice? | No, but the heavy D3D/DInput/Miles/Bink is entirely in GameEngineDevice |
| Single frame step? | No built-in method; call `GameEngine::update()` once per tick; `execute()` is just a `while(!m_quitting)` loop calling `update()` |
| Object iteration | `TheGameLogic->getFirstObject()` + `obj->getNextObject()` linked list; O(1) lookup via `findObjectByID()` |
| Player iteration | `ThePlayerList->getPlayerCount()` + `getNthPlayer(i)` |
| Command injection | `TheMessageStream->appendMessage(type)` + append typed args; or directly to `TheCommandList` |
| Replay mechanism | `MSG_BEGIN_NETWORK_MESSAGES`..`MSG_END_NETWORK_MESSAGES` recorded to `.rep` file by frame; played back by re-injecting into `TheCommandList` |
| Critical headless blocker | `TheAudio->isMusicAlreadyLoaded()` must return `true` or engine immediately sets `m_quitting = TRUE` |
| Entry point | `GameMain()` in `GameEngine/Source/Common/GameMain.cpp` calls `CreateGameEngine()` then `init()` then `execute()` |
| Module/ThingFactory | Cannot be easily stubbed — these factories create all unit behavior modules; W3D-specific factories assume W3D asset loading. This is the deepest coupling point |
